> Please review the architectural decisions and the folder structure. Specifically, verify if the distinction between tenantless B2C and tenant-based B2B users using Supabase aligns with your data modeling expectations.

## Proposed Architecture & Decisions

### 1. Hybrid B2C & B2B (Tenant model)
To maintain a **single codebase** while supporting both B2C and B2B users:
- **Database level**: We will rely on Supabase organizations/tenants. B2B users will have an `organization_id` tied to a tenant, whereas B2C users might have a `null` organization or belong to a global 'Individual' tenant. Row Level Security (RLS) policies in PostgreSQL will scope data correctly.
- **Application level**: We will use route groups and a shared App Shell. Features will be feature-flagged based on the user's tenant capabilities or role.

### 2. UI & Design System
- **calm, professional, mentor-like UI**: Minimalist colors, rounded corners, soft shadows, ample whitespace. Instead of stark primary colors, we will configure Tailwind to use soft blues, sage greens, or slate tones.
- **shadcn/ui**: Will provide accessible, unstyled baseline components that we theme to the mentor-like aesthetic.
- **Mobile-friendly**: We will build the App Shell layouts to use off-canvas sidebars on smaller breakpoints and ensure Recharts are responsive.

### 3. Folder Structure & Route Groups
We will utilize the Next.js `src/` directory and App Router route groups for clean separation:

```text
src/
  app/
    (public)/           # Public landing, marketing, and onboarding
      layout.tsx        # Public navigation header/footer
      page.tsx          # /
      login/page.tsx    # /login
      signup/page.tsx   # /signup
    (auth)/             # Authenticated User App Shell
      layout.tsx        # Collapsible Sidebar & Topnav
      dashboard/page.tsx
      assessment/page.tsx
      radar/page.tsx
      pathways/page.tsx
      growth-plan/page.tsx
      coach/page.tsx
      reassessment/page.tsx
      marketplace/page.tsx
    (admin)/            # Admin & Institutional App Shell
      layout.tsx        # Admin-specific sidebar
      admin/page.tsx
      admin/analytics/page.tsx
  components/
    ui/                 # shadcn/ui generic components
    shared/             # Reusable business components (e.g., RadarChartCard)
    layout/             # Sidebar, Header, Footer
  lib/
    utils.ts            # Tailwind generic utils
    supabase/           # client.ts, server.ts
  types/                # TypeScript global models (User, Profile, etc.)
  services/             # Data fetching & mutations
  hooks/                # Reusable React hooks
```

